===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The superior or head of an [[abbey]] or [[monastery]]. {{defdate|First attested around the early 12<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref>{{R:CDOE|page=2}}</ref><ref>{{R:SOED5|page=3}}</ref>
#: ''The newly appointed '''abbot''' decided to take a tour of the abbey with the cardinal's emissary.''
# A [[layman]] who received the [[abbey]]'s revenues, after the closing of the monasteries.
# {{lb|en|archaic|British slang}} A brothel-owner's [[husband]] or [[lover]].<ref name=barrere>{{R:Barrere|volume=1|page=3}}</ref><ref name=farmer>{{R:Farmer|volume=1|pages=4}}</ref>
# {{lb|en|archaic|British slang}} A [[ponce]]; a man employed by a [[prostitute]] to find [[client]]s, and who may also act as a [[bodyguard]] or equivalent to a [[bouncer]].<ref name=barrere /><ref name=farmer />

